(1, 1, '2015-05-07 11:43:46', '2015-05-07 11:43:46', 'Where server-side processing comes into play is when you have very large quantities of data that you wish to display in the table (millions of rows for example). At these levels, sending the data to the client, and then having Javascript process the data can involve noticeable overhead, will result in poor performance of the end application. In server-side processing mode, all ordering, searching, etc. of the data is handed off to the server which can make use of the database engines available there, which are highly tuned for exactly these kinds of operations', 'Server-side processing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world', '', '', '2015-05-16 04:07:04', '2015-05-16 04:07:04', '', 0, 'http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 1),
