(80, 1, '2015-06-13 16:28:01', '2015-06-13 16:28:01', '<a href="http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/reading1.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-79" src="http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/reading1-300x247.jpg" alt="reading1" width="605" height="498" /></a>\r\nI come from a family of five people : my parents , my two younger brothers and I . My mother works as a nurse in a big hospital. She has to work a long hours and once a week she has to work on a night shift . My father is a biologist . He works from 8 am to 5 pm in a lab , but sometimes when there is a project he doesn’t come home until very late at night . Althought my parents are very busy at work, they try to spend as muck time for their childrens as possible . It is generally believed the “ men make house and women make home “ but in my family , both parents jiin hands to give us a nice hoyuse and a happy hime.\r\n\r\nMy mother is a very caring woman . She takes the responsibility for running the household . She is always the first one to get up in the morning to make sure that we leave home for school with breakfast and in suitable clothers . In the afternoon , after hospital , she rushes to the market , the hurries home so that dinner is readdy on the table by the time Dad gets homr. Dad is always willing to give a hand with cleaning the house . Unlike most men , he enjoys cooking. Sometimes , at weekends . he cooks us some special dishes. His eel soup is better than any other suops I have ever eatáº¹n.\r\n\r\nAs I am now in my final year at the secondary school, and in my attempt to win a place at university , I am under a lot of study pressure. However. Being the eldest child and the only daughter in the family I try ti help with household chores. My main reponsibility is to wash the dishes and take out the garbege. I also look after the boys , who are quite active and mischievous sometimes, but most of the time they are quite obedient and hard-working . They love joining my father in mending things around the house ar weekend.\r\n\r\nWe are a very close-knit family and very supportive of one another. We often share our feelings , and whenever problems come up. We discuss them frank and find solutions quickly. We always feek safe and secure in our family. It is a base frim which we can go into the world with confidence .\r\n<div><strong>Task 2</strong>.Answer the questions.</div>\r\n<div>1. How busy are the parents in the passage?</div>\r\n<div>2. How caring is the mother?</div>\r\n<div>3. How do the father and the daughter share the household chores?</div>\r\n<div>4. What is the daughter attempting to do after secondary school?</div>\r\n<div>5. Why do the children feel they are safe and secure in their family?</div>', 'Home Life', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-13 16:28:01', '2015-06-13 16:28:01', '', 62, 'http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/2015/06/13/62-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(81, 1, '2015-06-13 17:01:45', '2015-06-13 17:01:45', '<a href="http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/reading1.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-79" src="http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/reading1-300x247.jpg" alt="reading1" width="605" height="498" /></a>\nI come from a family of five people : my parents , my two younger brothers and I . My mother works as a nurse in a big hospital. She has to work a long hours and once a week she has to work on a night shift . My father is a biologist. He works from 8 am to 5 pm in a lab , but sometimes when there is a project he does not come home until very late at night. Although my parents are very busy at work, they try to spend as muck time for their children as possible. It is generally believed the “ men make house and women make home “ but in my family, both parents join hands to give us a nice house and a happy home.\n\nMy mother is a very caring woman . She takes the responsibility for running the household. She is always the first one to get up in the morning to make sure that we leave home for school with breakfast and in suitable clothes . In the afternoon, after hospital, she rushes to the market , the hurries home so that dinner is ready on the table by the time Dad gets home. Dad is always willing to give a hand with cleaning the house. Unlike most men, he enjoys cooking. Sometimes, at weekends he cooks us some special dishes. His eel soup is better than any other soups I have ever eaten\n\nAs I am now in my final year at the secondary school, and in my attempt to win a place at university, I am under a lot of study pressure. However, being the eldest child and the only daughter in the family I try to help with household chores. My main responsibility is to wash the dishes and take out the garbage. I also look after the boys, who are quite active and mischievous sometimes, but most of the time they are quite obedient and hard-working . They love joining my father in mending things around the house at weekend.\n\nWe are a very close-knit family and very supportive of one another. We often share our feelings, and whenever problems come up. We discuss them frank and find solutions quickly. We always feel safe and secure in our family. It is a base from which we can go into the world with confidence .\n\n1. How busy are the parents in the passage?\n2. How caring is the mother?\n3. How do the father and the daughter share the household chores?\n4. What is the daughter attempting to do after secondary school?\n5. Why do the children feel they are safe and secure in their family?\n<div class="form-grammar">\n- shift (v):  move or change from one position or direction to another, especially slightly.\n- night shift (n): a period in the night during which a particular group of people work.\n- responsibility (n): something that it is your job or duty to deal with\n- as ... as possible\n- household  (n):  a group of people, often a family, who live together\n- willing  (v) to do something:  to be happy to do something if it is needed\n- pressure (n): the force you produce when you press something.\n- garbage (n): unwanted things that you throw away.\n- mischievous  (a):  behaving in a way, or describing behaviour, that is slightly bad but is not intended to cause - serious harm or damage.\n- obedient (a): doing, or willing to do, what you have been told to do by someone in authority.\n- supportive (a): showing agreement and giving encouragement.\n- frank (a): honest, sincere, and telling the truth, even when this might be awkward or make other people - uncomfortable.\n- secure (a): positioned or fixed firmly and correctly and therefore not likely to move, fall, or break.\n- behaviour (n): he way that someone behaves.\n</div>', 'Home Life', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-13 17:01:45', '2015-06-13 17:01:45', '', 62, 'http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/2015/06/13/62-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(82, 1, '2015-06-13 16:31:45', '2015-06-13 16:31:45', '<a href="http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/reading1.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-79" src="http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/reading1-300x247.jpg" alt="reading1" width="605" height="498" /></a>\r\nI come from a family of five people : my parents , my two younger brothers and I . My mother works as a nurse in a big hospital. She has to work a long hours and once a week she has to work on a night shift . My father is a biologist . He works from 8 am to 5 pm in a lab , but sometimes when there is a project he does not come home until very late at night . Although my parents are very busy at work, they try to spend as muck time for their children as possible . It is generally believed the “ men make house and women make home “ but in my family , both parents join hands to give us a nice house and a happy home.\r\n\r\nMy mother is a very caring woman . She takes the responsibility for running the household . She is always the first one to get up in the morning to make sure that we leave home for school with breakfast and in suitable clothes . In the afternoon , after hospital , she rushes to the market , the hurries home so that dinner is ready on the table by the time Dad gets home. Dad is always willing to give a hand with cleaning the house . Unlike most men , he enjoys cooking. Sometimes , at weekends . he cooks us some special dishes. His eel soup is better than any other soups I have ever eaten.\r\n\r\nAs I am now in my final year at the secondary school, and in my attempt to win a place at university , I am under a lot of study pressure. However. Being the eldest child and the only daughter in the family I try ti help with household chores. My main responsibility is to wash the dishes and take out the garbage. I also look after the boys , who are quite active and mischievous sometimes, but most of the time they are quite obedient and hard-working . They love joining my father in mending things around the house ar weekend.\r\n\r\nWe are a very close-knit family and very supportive of one another. We often share our feelings , and whenever problems come up. We discuss them frank and find solutions quickly. We always feel safe and secure in our family. It is a base from which we can go into the world with confidence .\r\n<div><strong>Task 2</strong>.Answer the questions.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>1. How busy are the parents in the passage?</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>2. How caring is the mother?</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>3. How do the father and the daughter share the household chores?</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>4. What is the daughter attempting to do after secondary school?</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>5. Why do the children feel they are safe and secure in their family?</div>', 'Home Life', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-13 16:31:45', '2015-06-13 16:31:45', '', 62, 'http://jerry-rosabella.rhcloud.com/2015/06/13/62-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
